---
const features = [
  {
    "id": "faq-1",
    "question": "Why choose Burrowin Electrical for residential electrical services?",
    "answer": "Burrowin Electrical is your trusted local electrician, providing expert residential electrical solutions across [Your Service Area]. We are committed to quality, safety, and affordability, ensuring your electrical needs are met with exceptional service and peace of mind."
  },
  {
    "id": "faq-2",
    "question": "What types of residential electrical services do you offer?",
    "answer": "We offer a comprehensive range of residential electrical services, including (but not limited to):\n* Repairs and maintenance\n* Installations (lighting, outlets, fixtures, etc.)\n* Safety inspections and upgrades\n* Panel replacements and rewiring\n* Smart home electrical integration\n* And much more!  \nContact us today to discuss your specific needs."
  },
  {
    "id": "faq-3",
    "question": "Do you offer emergency electrical services?",
    "answer": "Yes, we understand that electrical emergencies can happen anytime. We offer 24/7 emergency electrical services to ensure your safety and get your home back up and running as quickly as possible."
  },
  {
    "id": "faq-4",
    "question": "How much do your electrical services cost?",
    "answer": "The cost of our services depends on the specific job and its requirements. We offer free consultations and upfront quotes to ensure transparency and allow you to make informed decisions."
  },
  {
    "id": "faq-5",
    "question": "Are your electricians licensed and insured?",
    "answer": "Absolutely! All our electricians are fully licensed, insured, and qualified to handle any residential electrical job safely and efficiently."
  },
  {
    "id": "faq-6",
    "question": "What are some signs that I need an electrician?",
    "answer": "Here are some common signs that you may need an electrician:\n* Flickering or dimming lights\n* Sparking outlets or switches\n* Tripping circuit breakers frequently\n* Buzzing or humming sounds from electrical components\n* Burning smell coming from electrical panels or outlets\n* Any concerns about the safety of your home's electrical system\nIf you experience any of these signs, don't hesitate to contact a qualified electrician."
  },
  {
    "id": "faq-7",
    "question": "How can I prevent electrical problems in my home?",
    "answer": "Here are some tips to prevent electrical problems:\n* Avoid overloading outlets and extension cords.\n* Regularly inspect your electrical cords and outlets for damage.\n* Don't attempt electrical work yourself unless you are a qualified electrician.\n* Schedule regular electrical inspections by a professional."
  },
  {
    "id": "faq-8",
    "question": "What should I do if I experience a power outage?",
    "answer": "First, check if your neighbors also have no power. If it's just your home, check your circuit breaker box and see if any breakers have tripped. Reset any tripped breakers and see if the power comes back on. If the power outage affects your entire neighborhood, contact your local power company."
  },
  {
    "id": "faq-9",
    "question": "What are the benefits of upgrading my home's electrical panel?",
    "answer": "Upgrading your electrical panel can offer several benefits, including:\n* Increased safety and reliability\n* Improved capacity to handle modern appliances and electronics\n* Potential increase in your home's value\nConsult with a qualified electrician to determine if an upgrade is right for your home."
  },
  {
    "id": "faq-10",
    "question": "How can I schedule an appointment with Burrowin Electrical?",
    "answer": "Scheduling an appointment is easy! You can call us at 0409 379 309, email us at [Your Email Address], or fill out our online contact form on our website [link to your website]."
  }

];
---

<section class="my-28">
  <div class="mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 w-full lg:max-w-7xl lg:px-8">
    <div class="grid gap-12 lg:grid-cols-3 lg:gap-8">
      <h4 id="components" class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-medium tracking-tight pt-2">FAQ's</h4>
      <div class="lg:col-span-2">
        <dl
          class="-mt-3"
          x-data="{ selected: null, toggle(value) { this.selected = this.selected === value ? null : value } }"
        >
          {
            features.map((feature, index) => (
              <div
                class="rounded-3xl px-4 transition hover:bg-slate-600/10"
                x-data={`{ id: ${index}, get isOpen() { return this.id === this.selected }, get isNextOpen() { return (this.id + 1) === this.selected } }`}
                x-bind:class="{ 'bg-slate-600/10 dark:bg-primary-400/10': isOpen }"
              >
                <dt
                  class="border-b text-lg transition"
                  x-cloak
                  x-bind:class="{ 'border-transparent': isOpen || isNextOpen, 'border-primary-900/10 dark:border-primary-300/10': !(isOpen || isNextOpen) }"
                >
                  <button
                    type="button"
                    class="group block w-full py-6 text-left transition focus-visible:outline-none"
                    aria-controls={feature.id}
                    x-on:click="toggle(id)"
                    aria-expanded="false"
                    x-bind:aria-expanded="isOpen.toString()"
                  >
                    <div class="group-focus-visible:outline-primary-950 dark:group-focus-visible:outline-primary-200 flex items-center justify-between rounded-3xl group-focus-visible:outline group-focus-visible:outline-2 group-focus-visible:outline-offset-2">
                      <span class="text-lg md:text-xl font-medium">{feature.question}</span>
                      <span class="ml-6 flex h-7 items-center">
                        <svg
                          class="text-primary-600 dark:text-primary-400 h-6 w-6 rotate-0 transform transition duration-200 ease-in-out"
                          x-bind:class="{ '-rotate-180': isOpen, 'rotate-0': !isOpen }"
                          xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
                          viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                          fill="currentColor"
                          aria-hidden="true"
                        >
                          <path d="M11.9997 13.1714L16.9495 8.22168L18.3637 9.63589L11.9997 15.9999L5.63574 9.63589L7.04996 8.22168L11.9997 13.1714Z" />
                        </svg>
                      </span>
                    </div>
                  </button>
                </dt>
                <dd class="pb-6 pr-6" id={feature.id} x-show="isOpen" x-cloak x-collapse>
                  <p class="text-primary-950/70 dark:text-primary-200/70 text-base xs:text-lg">
                    {feature.answer}
                  </p>
                </dd>
              </div>
            ))
          }
        </dl>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
